Abstract: Creates the Avondale and Waggaman Economic Development District in
Jefferson Parish.
Proposed law creates the Avondale and Waggaman Economic Development District as a
political subdivision in Jefferson Parish to provide for cooperative economic and community
development among the district, the parish, the state, and the owners of property in the
district. Provides for district boundaries.
Proposed law provides that the district is governed by a seven-member board of
commissioners composed as follows:
(1) One member appointed by the Avondale Civic Association who is a representative
of the association.
(2) One member appointed by the Waggaman Civic Associations who is a representative
of the association.
(3) One member appointed by the S1 Civic Association who is a representative of the
association.
(4) One member appointed by the Kennedy Heights Civic Association who is a
representative of the association.
(5) The member of the La. Senate whose district encompasses all or the greater portion
of the area of the district or his designee.
(6) The member of the La. House of Representatives whose district encompasses all or
the greater portion of the area of the district or his designee.
(7) The member of the governing authority of the parish of Jefferson who represents
District No. 3 or his designee.
